cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.SY

This paper discusses a revocation mechanism for TLS, which is a security protocol used in network communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a framework that involves middleboxes, which are network devices, indicating that cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions scalability challenges, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The proposed framework also involves accountability and minimizing overhead, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
